kdl.prox.datagen2.structure
Class SyntheticGraphIID

java.lang.Object
  kdl.prox.datagen2.structure.SyntheticGraphIID

public class SyntheticGraphIID
extends java.lang.Object

Creates a random graph, with nodes with a degree specified in degreeDistribs or objectSpec There are two types of nodes, S and T. Saves their type in objectType attribute (and a linkType for the connections between them.)

NOTE: It assumes the database is empty, but initialized!

SyntheticGraphIID

public SyntheticGraphIID(int numCoreObjs,
                         java.lang.Object[][] degreeDistribs)
Generate generate S-T object structure with varying degrees of T objects for each S object.

Parameters:
numCoreObjs - the number of S objects to be created
degreeDistribs - probability distribution over degree distributions for the core objects. it's an array of arrays where the inner arrays are pairs containing a Double (the probability for the following distribution) and the Distribution the probability appplies to.
Throws:
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if types in degreeDistribs don't match the {Double, Distribution} pattern, or if probabilities in degreeDistribs don't sum to 1.0

SyntheticGraphIID

public SyntheticGraphIID(java.lang.Integer[][] objectSpec)
Generate a fixed structure based on the number of core objects presented. This method will generate S-T structure with a fixed number of Ts for each S. For example, an object spec that contains

2 4 3 2

will create 2 S objects connected to 4 T objects, add 3 S objects connected to 2 T objects.

Parameters:
objectSpec - specifies the number of S's and for each S the number of T's
